one behind the other, but not one of them dared to speak. Then the
Tsarevich Ivan bowed low before his father and said              Dear
Father-Gosudar! if none will take it upon him to render thee this
paltry little service, give me thy blessing on my journey. I will go, I
will seek my sisters, nor have I need of any royal gift from thee to
enable me to do it.                     Good!        replied Tsar
Umnaya Golova;        my blessing go with thee. Take also of my
treasures, silver and gold and precious stones, and if thou requirest
