"pb208">208]not? for Martin wanted to marry, and the bride
of his choice was not his like in birth, for she was a king       s
daughter. So he consulted his mother, and sent her away as his
matchmaker, and said to her,        Go to the King himself, and woo for
me the thrice-lovely Princess.                     Alas! my dear
son,        said his old mother,               twould be far better for
thee if thou wert to chop thine own wood. a class="noteref" id=
"xd20e1418src" href="#xd20e1418" name="xd20e1418src">4 But what art
thou thinking of? How can I go to the King and ask him for his daughter
