Then it was that Jurka and Vaska remembered how little Martin had
saved them from an evil death, and they came and laid their heads
together about it. Jurka growled and snarled, and was ready to tear
every one to bits, for his master       s sake; but Vaska purred and
hummed and scratched himself behind the ear with his velvet paw, and
