of Thrice-ten, whither she had told the twelve youths to carry her.
They ran into the kingdom, went to the palace, and made friends with
all the dogs and cats there, asked them [ a id=
"pb216" href="#pb216" name="pb216">216]all about the
Princess       s ways, and turned the conversation to the subject of
the enchanted ring; but no one could give them certain information
about it. But one day it happened that Vaska went a-hunting in the
